rComments: She is super nice and caring. She mainly reads off the slides and posts them online so attendance isn't mandatory, but recommended. Lectures can be boring but the project is very interesting. Pretty easy class overall.

I think she's fine, be present in class, listen when she presents powerpoints (makes it a lot easier when it comes to studying). On the other hand, her classes are boring, same tone in her voice, isn't really funny. Grade wise ? don't underestimate anything and study for exams and you'll get an easy A (only if you don't underestimate the class.

Could be a more bit more demanding. I wish we learned more. All of the information is relevant, but not new to our (young) generation who already knows much of the content seeing as how we have to fix the environment... If you're looking for an easy A take this course.  That doesn't doesn't mean a free A - there is some studying to do. She is kind!

I had taken ENV1501 as an elective class, a mandatory French credit. I was surprised to see that the Professor seemed mostly lost for the first 3 weeks of class, both with her lack of understanding of uOttawa systems, as well as the lack of course material and clarity. Unfortunately, I would not recommend her. She's nice though :)
